FT  02 JUL 93 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
JOHANNESBURG rallied on a weaker rand and a late surge in the gold price,
the gold index hitting its best level in over three years as it rose 33, or
1.7 per cent to 1,943. Vaal Reefs and De Beers, between them, saw almost
R40m of stock change hands as they rose R10 to R348, and R1.25 to R80.50
respectively. Industrials lost 14 to 4,682 and the overall index added 21 to
4,099.
